Subject: RE: [VB] Detergent oil, new engine?, When?

Sludging will also occur in our air cooled engines if the case is not vented properly to a sufficent vacum source.Keep the road draft tube clean and with the proper boot installed.

Another cause of sludging is extended service intervals.Change the oil at 4000 miles max,new vehicles can sometimes get away with longer service intervals but the oil in these engines is not subject to the same enviornment as in an air cooled motor.

